      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "OPAL ONYX (1) has been in the minors the last two, the latest showing strong pace early but gathered in and finished a 0.8 lengths second over 340m Hobart in 19.45. Hard to knock her form from this box, unbeaten in two starts. Top prospect. AUSSIE PABLO (2) doesn't have the best strike-rate but recent form is sound. Has hit the frame the last two runs, the latest when third (26.44) at Hobart. Solid record here winning five races. Has performed well from this box with a win and three minor placings to his name from six starts. Nicely placed to grab a well-deserved win. TICKING OVER (8) shapes as hard to beat after winning last start over the 340m at Hobart in a handy 19.47. Harder here but expected to feature again. DEADLY STREET (4) has been in the placings at his last two runs, most recently when second (19.63) in a Grade 5 over 340m at Hobart.",
